The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports
Archives
 India in Lanka
Colombo: Fixtures for the next years India-Sri Lanka cricket series to be held in the island nation will be finalised in January, Sri Lanka Cricket authorities said. We will finalise the schedule for the Sri Lanka cricket series, slated for June, around January next year. We will be holding discussions with the BCCI secretary, Niranjan Shah, and other officials, Sri Lanka cricket secretary K. Madhivanan said. India are scheduled to play the hosts in three Tests and five ODIs. 
